# Backend Data Layer (`Code.gs`)

## Spreadsheet Binding

- Use the explicit spreadsheet ID from `PROJECT_TRACKER_SPREADSHEET_ID` / script properties.
- Never silently create or fall back to another workbook.
- Throw errors that name the expected sheet, accepted aliases, and available tabs.

## Sheets and Headers

- Resolve tabs via `SHEET_ALIASES` (e.g. `Projects`, `Project Database` → `PROJECTS`).
- Match headers with normalized names; preserve physical column indexes when mapping rows.
- Use `alignSheetHeaders_()` when canonical column order matters; test on production-shaped sheets first.
- Ignore blank header columns during mapping, but do not drop unnamed physical columns before `rowToObject_`.

## Read / Write Pipeline

Every client-facing read must pass through transport sanitization:

```javascript
// ✅ GOOD — safe for google.script.run
return rows.map(function (row) {
  return sanitizeRecordForTransport_(row.data);
});

// ❌ BAD — native Date/boolean/object can break the bridge
return rows.map(function (row) { return row.data; });
```

Trace "saved but not visible" through: write → flush → read → map → serialize → client handler → filter → render.

## Normalization (Separate Concerns)

| Purpose | Rule |
|---|---|
| Display | Blank → `N/A` in UI only |
| Persistence | Store empty string or canonical value, not display tokens |
| Search | Empty query → `''`, never `N/A` |
| Transport | Dates as formatted strings; booleans as `'TRUE'`/`'FALSE'` |

## IDs and Audit

- Generate system IDs on the backend only (`PROJ-YYYY-###`, `SPROJ-YYYY-###`, record IDs).
- Validate payloads and required IDs before accessing sheets or properties.
- Log audit entries with human-readable field names and old/new values.

## Public API Functions

- Guard against manual Apps Script editor calls with missing arguments.
- Return structured diagnostics, not opaque failures.
